Pitch Outcomes and Zone Heatmaps
Analyzing Pitch Outcomes by Type and Location
This project focuses on visualizing and analyzing pitch outcomes for various pitch types and locations using Python, Matplotlib, and Seaborn. The goal is to provide actionable insights for player performance and pitch effectiveness by generating tables and heatmaps.

Features
1. Pitch Outcomes Table
Overview: A detailed table summarizing pitch outcomes (e.g., strike swinging, strike called, chased pitch, ball in play) by pitch type.
Visualization: Generates a clean, structured table using Matplotlib.
2. Zone Heatmap
Overview: Heatmaps displaying pitch effectiveness across different strike zones.
Visualization: Zone-specific performance of pitch types with annotations for easy interpretation.
Customization: Adjustable labels and color schemes.
Technologies Used
Python: Core programming language.
Pandas: Data manipulation and grouping.
Matplotlib: Table visualization and heatmap generation.
Seaborn: For heatmaps and enhanced visuals.
